The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will set up a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday's strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since rail traffic will be completely stopped and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon the League Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday that they will hold jointly with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
Likewise, the strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Machinists will be constituted, which will coordinate Monday's actions.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while participating unions will strike indefinitely on Monday if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not inform about the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call to strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
Based on the National Assembly's Monday agenda, it is also possible that the public health law will only be voted on in the very late hours of the night, or perhaps close to midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways, work will be stopped indefinitely, in the morning a part of the collective transport in Budapest and more than half of the interurban bus transport of the Volán companies may stop.
At the same time, half of the roads will be closed in many parts of the country.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some unions announced their strike indefinitely, others for a definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are traveling on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, those of Budapest Airport from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m., the LIGA Unions of the Electricity and Thermal Energy Industry will hold a four-hour strike.  the Teachers' Unions called for a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Doctors will go on national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Trade Union of Health and Social Sector Workers (SDTSSS), which is part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new way of calculating pensions that will come into force next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions, the possibility that occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Unions, does not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway lateral lines and expects a different proposal.
Political Capital: The risk increased in the country by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysing Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk in Hungary and the region in several respects.
The company's "risk warning" writes: In relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between Hungary's Roma and non-Roma population, violent ethnic clashes may occur even in the short term."
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They stated that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life handed over the public debate on the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of violent conflicts.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
They remind us that: since the autumn of 2006, the reorganization of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary received increasing publicity and impetus and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been formed in the country that define themselves as "associations of national self-defense".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, that is, the State" - they add.
They affirmed: all this occurs in accordance with the method that tries to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on society's discontent with politics and political parties.
For highlighting the civil and the form of association in the case of these associations not only serves to avoid the legal problems of legal registration, but is at the same time also a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the activity of the Hungarian Guard is a risk factor also from the point of view of neighbourly relations.
