The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and it has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - which next year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Not even in the EU or North America are the holidays unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holidays, state holidays and public holidays.
The festive days are mainly related to religious festivals and historical anniversaries.
We celebrate the New Year too: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are holidays - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven holidays written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, commemorative day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20 we celebrate the founding of the State, on May 1 the labor holiday, on November 1 and 2 we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country are two-day festivals Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the holiday there is only one working day.
In exchange for the weekends extended like this, during the previous Saturdays you can not be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when you have to work exactly in exchange for the day directly before or after the party.
This legal norm is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not obligatory, however, for service companies and institutions which, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during the festive days.
This year the order of work can only be altered around the holidays at the end of the year: from December 24 life in the country practically stops, since according to experiences, most people "make bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our parties will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda around the labor festival will be modified so that then, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in exchange Friday, May 2 will be a holiday.
The other change is related to the holiday of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, we will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the year that comes during the end of year party can be rested, since from December 24 you will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six little deterrents to sour the lives of your colleagues
Emails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that happen to us without realizing it: all of them are part of our daily Folklore at work.
You have to decide if you adapt to the small discomforts or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Councils.
$isculpa, I forgot to let you know that you have been sought out from the marketing department" - says one of your colleagues.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
In the best case you feel it and try to repair the matter, maybe call the marketing department to tell them that you forgot to deliver the message (this is the least usual solution).
Most of the time the matter is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding to embarrassing explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can embitter the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that isn't yours?
There is nothing more irritating than when you want to pick up a document, an office supplies or your phone and do not find them.
Do you remember that yesterday you placed the stapler on the table, but for this morning it disappeared?
Do you find your lost pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Don't take anything away from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly get mad at you for stealing their things.
Do not take envelopes or post-it notes from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out ahead of time.
Do you gossip about the private lives of your colleagues?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Don't pass on to everyone the information (guesses) you have about the particular lives of your colleagues!
Don't abuse your colleague's trust when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, although others also know things about him.
Are you leaving sick leave unjustifiably?
When you phone the office and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or good, you feel that day you prefer to rest; Think about how others must do your work, your tasks that cannot be postponed, your work by term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you already know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you should stay at home, let them know, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to confront your absence the next day.
Humming, giggling, phone calls
Are you involved in your work, but the laughter of your colleagues abruptly takes you out of it?
Have you involuntarily overheard a phone conversation that would have been better not to listen to?
Don't disturb your colleagues with your humming, singing, loud conversations (less when you do them above their head), kicking, constant profanity, expressing your discontent out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if they are not delving into a project right now (writing, planning, organizing).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don't blame others if you haven't finished something on time, forgot to send an important letter or message!
Do not allude to the chaos that eventually reigns in the office, or the noise that your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can repair your fault!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and slippers - very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Do not wear a comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Don't be messy, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing smart, elegant and beautiful everyday clothes when your occupation demands it!
