600,000 people failed to change their driver's license
Six hundred thousand drivers missed the date and therefore failed to change their old driving license whose validity ends at the end of the year.
Today is the last day when people can request the change so that officials give them time until the end of the year to issue the new card.
However, the Ministry is not afraid that after New Year hundreds of thousands of drivers will find themselves on the roads without a valid license.
According to traffic, the license has not been changed mainly by those who no longer even want to drive.
While in the villages they announce a rapid decrease in the change of cards, the offices of the metropolis are full of applications and the interest in the new card has increased.
The City Council estimates around 2,000 customers per day.
In the queues you wait half an hour.
In Prague, around 140,000 drivers have not yet issued the new licence.
The issuance of a new card lasts twenty days.
However, it is possible to request the issuance of the card within a shorter period of five days.
But in that case the driver must pay five hundred crowns.
Drivers who must change their license and do not reach until the end of the year, but will go out on the roads without the valid license will risk a fine from January.
The offender shall pay a maximum of two thousand crowns.
The policeman can fix the infraction with a warning.
In case of an administrative offence the fine will amount to 2,500 crowns.
According to the above information, anyone who does not go anywhere could receive a fine.
They could presumably pay up to 30,000 kroner.
The Ministry appealed to the offices to pay moderate fines of one thousand crowns, at most.
According to the spokesperson of the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, fines of one thousand crowns do not threaten anyone.
According to him, the driver's license is a document in which people can decide if they want it or not.
It is not the identity card that each person must have valid.
People who do not want to drive should hand over their driver's license.
Simply bring it or send it by registered mail to the municipal offices.
At the end of the year, the cards issued during the years 1964 and 1993 ceased to be valid.
However, drivers will have to gradually change the other types of driving license.
People with the document between 1994 and 2000 have up to three years to change it.
The validity of the card that was issued between 2001 and 2004 ends in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, this is about 2.6 million more documents.
