Other places metamorphose into beauty, for example, Trinidad.
Because tourism brings so much necessary money, its development is guaranteed.
In the last fifteen years new hotels grew not only in Havana but also in Varadero, on the coast of the province of Holguín and on islets such as Cayo Coco, Cayo Guillermo and others.
Cuba still offers a curiosity that is unique in the world and that is highly valued by railway lovers.
Sugarcane is transported from the immense plantations to the sugar factories by narrow roads in steam or electric engines.
Its garages for dozens of years were not discovered and now they are there, machines that work and whose sister models that exist in other parts of the world are only found in museums.
