But I don't see such a change," he added.
Doubt grows
State debt creates debts in the central government and arises, above all, from the accumulation of the state budget deficit.
State debt is paid through treasury bonds, government bonds, direct credits or for example loans from the European Investment Bank.
The internal indebtedness of the state grew this year from 38,500 million to 719,400 million crowns.
Foreign debt has so far grown from SEK 1.7 billion to SEK 123.3 billion.
The so-called negotiable state debt at the end of September contained 803.3 billion kroner z since June was reduced by 13.7 billion kroner.
The average maturity of government debt increased by 6.5 years.
"Total year-on-year debt from the first to the third quarters grew by 13 percent, which is huge given how the economy works.
