It is bad that the debt grows but on the other hand it shows that it is going to be negotiated until there is a pension reform, "said Pikora.
Better than expected
From the strategy of payments and management of the state debt for the year 2007 it is clear that the government planned to lend 159.2 billion kroner this year.
At the beginning of December, the ministry reduced the plan by SEK 152.8 billion thanks to improved state budget developments.
The amount is composed, above all, of the deficit of the state budget that this year will be 76 million crowns in vey of the expected 91,300 million crowns.
The remainder consists of maximum resources planned for the Czech Consolidation Agency with about SEK 13.3 billion, the reserve of SEK 10 billion for pension payments, SEK 43 billion to finance state obligations and SEK 1.8 billion in payments on European Investment Bank loans.
