Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
Parallel to its parliamentary process, which ended today with the vote by Congress on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of entities so that markets function efficiently.
The Mifid, which modifies the Securities Market Law, involves the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the different supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which join securities firms, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with existing stock exchange managers.
The Law also obliges investment firms to disclose in the market information on the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economy Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it stands out that securitized debts are considered as a "complex" financial instrument given their high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the debt of US subprime mortgages.
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can carry out 30 years after the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work as an employee, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting clients to different investment companies at the same time.
