The award for best actor went to Viggo Mortensen for his role as a driver of a boss of the Russian mafia in London, in David Cronenberg's film Eastern Promises.
Ray Winstone, who has a reputation for playing hardball, received the Richard Jarris Award for his contribution to British cinema.
The fifties, whose films include Scum, Nil By Mouth and Sexy Beast, is currently filming the Indiana Jones sequel "Kingdom of the Crystal Skull."
Winstone said he was proud to receive that award, named in honor of Camelot and Harry Potter star Harris, who died in 2002.
"It was people like Richard Harrris and Albert Finney who opened doors for people like me," he said.
