Is the subprime mortgage crisis infecting the American credit card market?
When there is blood in the water, it is natural for dorsal fins to swim excitedly around.
Now that the American housing market is in crisis, predators have their sights set on the country's credit card market.
Analysts at Goldman Sachs estimate that credit card losses could reach $99 million if the subprime mortgage crisis spreads other forms of consumer credit.
Signs of contagion are already seen.
