Richard Gere only lacks more cynicism.
The two films "The Hunting Party" and "Moerderischer Frieden" are again devoted to the war in the Balkans.
But the two were not very convinced.
Either the concepts are fixed a lot in actions and shots or the two films are too exciting.
Richard Gere with his "The Hunting Party" can't help in this case either.
At the beginning there was good news: Karadzic and Mladic, the war criminals, continue to hide in the Balkan mountains, but precisely there, in the dark interior of the country during the Bosnian war, the actor Richard Gere was discovered again.
