"The Hunting Party", despite this triumph, along with "Moerderischer Frieden" which is the German production and will also be presented this week, turn out to be just a series of unsuccessful films about the war in the Balkans.
You can narrate the film "Moerderischer Frieden" in a few words: it is about two German soldiers in Kosovo (Adrian Topol, Max Riemelt) who want to save a Serb from Kosovo snipers, one of them acts very fast and that also leads him to fall in love with her.
The sense of the film is lost by the actions and shootings, although we celebrate that the Serbs are not once again presented as the only culprits.
The film is like the German series "Alarm fuer Cobra 11" without a motorway, but in a war situation.
In the example of "The Hunting Party" you can investigate, because there was never really a good movie about the war in the Balkans.
At another point, with another director and with another screenwriter (Richard Shepard in two charges), the story about American reporters in the war who leave to detect a Serb war criminal named "fox", could probably be a new "Apocalypse Now".
Thus, the stories are surprisingly similar: the small teams go twice to the mountain to carry out something that the army cannot do and each time it is a crazy trip.
